  // Social: "30 million American adults have vision loss — and almost nobody writes setup guides for them. Here is the one. Zoom, bold text, Smart Invert, VoiceOver, Speak Screen, Magnifier with yellow-on-black filters, Be My Eyes, Seeing AI, and the free training from Hadley Institute that nobody tells you about. Your phone can work brilliantly for you. Here is how."
  // Newsletter: "One in six adults in the United States lives with some form of vision loss — and the number grows every year as the population ages. Despite being one of the largest underserved groups in consumer technology, almost nobody writes plain-English setup guides aimed at them. This one is. We walk through every meaningful low-vision feature on iPhone and Android — the zoom gesture that is faster than any menu, text and contrast settings, Smart Invert, the screen readers, Speak Screen, the Magnifier with its color filters, dictation, voice control, and the small handful of apps (Be My Eyes, Seeing AI) that genuinely change daily life. We also cover hardware choices, specialized phones worth knowing about, and the free training offered by the Hadley Institute that almost nobody has heard of. These are practical, no self-pity, all doable. You can do this."
